WEBVTT

00:03.040 --> 00:07.909
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven--

00:08.080 --> 00:11.072
-What are you doing?
-Masticating.

00:12.280 --> 00:13.872
-What?
-Don't worry.

00:14.040 --> 00:17.032
-lt doesn't mean what you think.
-What do you think l think?

00:17.200 --> 00:19.077
You know.

00:19.840 --> 00:22.308
Okay, l know what l know.

00:22.480 --> 00:23.754
What do you know?

00:23.920 --> 00:27.549
l know you're supposed to masticate
your food 20 times before you swallow.

00:27.720 --> 00:29.950
Yeah, but what about the other thing?

00:30.120 --> 00:32.156
What other thing?

00:32.320 --> 00:34.550
The thing you thought l was thinking.

00:35.080 --> 00:37.071
l'm sorry, Dad. You lost me.

00:39.400 --> 00:42.153
-Morning.
-Oh, morning. lsn't this your day off?

00:42.320 --> 00:45.153
-lt is. But l need to talk to Charlie.
-Well, good luck.

00:45.320 --> 00:48.278
He got home, had a bowl of chili,
threw up and went to bed.

00:48.440 --> 00:51.557
He probably threw up
because he didn't masticate enough.

00:53.640 --> 00:56.279
Hey, potty-mouth,
there's a lady present.

00:56.440 --> 00:58.158
Why don't you tell me
what you need. . .

00:58.320 --> 01:02.472
. . .then you can go enjoy your day off by
spreading sunshine and cheer to others.

01:02.640 --> 01:04.915
lt's about the house.
l should wait for Charlie.

01:05.080 --> 01:07.230
l live here too. What's the problem?

01:08.320 --> 01:09.355
l'll wait.

01:09.520 --> 01:12.637
Oh, for God's sakes, pretend l'm Charlie.
Talk to me.

01:13.240 --> 01:14.912
Okay.

01:15.640 --> 01:17.039
Charlie, l thought it over.

01:17.200 --> 01:20.192
lf you want me to kill your brother,
l'll need the cash up front.

01:23.720 --> 01:27.030
-Very amusing.
-Thanks, l've been taking an improv class.

01:27.200 --> 01:29.077
Okay, here's the deal.

01:29.240 --> 01:31.435
l got five brothers and sisters.

01:31.600 --> 01:35.718
l'm the middle child, which probably
explains why l'm such a people pleaser.

01:37.760 --> 01:40.320
Anyhow, my brother Philip,
he's the second oldest.

01:40.480 --> 01:44.837
He's in the roadside fireworks business,
which is, as you might expect, seasonal.

01:46.320 --> 01:50.313
This creates some economic uncertainty,
which has strained his marriage.

01:50.480 --> 01:54.155
Perhaps not as much as him boinking
his wife's half-sister.

01:54.320 --> 01:56.356
But it's a snowball effect.

01:56.520 --> 01:58.670
Anyway, to make a long story short.

01:58.840 --> 02:00.273
Too late.

02:01.000 --> 02:04.356
Fair enough. Berta one, Zippy one.

02:05.040 --> 02:09.636
Anyway, Philip can't live at his house
because technically it's a crime scene.

02:11.280 --> 02:15.068
-Which is why l wanted to ask Charlie--
-You want your brother to stay here?

02:15.240 --> 02:16.639
Oh, don't be stupid.

02:16.800 --> 02:18.074
He's staying at my place. . .

02:18.240 --> 02:21.471
. . .trying to wean himself off the meth
and the codeine and whatnot.

02:21.640 --> 02:24.438
l wanna stay here for a couple of days.

02:26.720 --> 02:30.918
-That's okay. l'll ask Charlie.
-No, you don't have to ask Charlie.

02:31.080 --> 02:32.638
You can ask me.

02:32.800 --> 02:34.472
Fine.

02:36.200 --> 02:37.792
Oh, you'd like an answer now.

02:37.960 --> 02:39.791
That'd be swell.

02:39.960 --> 02:43.589
Well, l would have to say. . .

02:43.760 --> 02:45.990
. . .after due consideration. . .

02:46.160 --> 02:51.439
. . .and taking into account all the factors
that are involved. . .

02:51.600 --> 02:56.754
. . .that it would be our pleasure
to have you.

02:56.920 --> 02:58.911
Super. Do you mind if l take your room?

02:59.680 --> 03:02.148
-My room? Gee, l--
-Trust me.

03:02.320 --> 03:05.153
You want me to have a room
with a private crapper.

03:08.520 --> 03:09.919
Okay. By all means.

03:10.400 --> 03:13.278
-Take my room. l'll bunk with Jake.
-Thanks.

03:13.440 --> 03:15.192
What do you mean
you'll bunk with Jake?

03:15.760 --> 03:18.354
-ls that a problem?
-Yes, l need my privacy.

03:18.520 --> 03:21.353
-For what?
-You know.

